li.al:
NAPMO shall be exempt from taxes and excise duties which form part of
		  the price of goods purchased by and of services rendered to NAPMO for its
		  official use;

NAPMO shall be exempt from motorvehicle tax on vehicles owned by
		  NAPMO for its official use. These vehicles will bear the RC registration
		  plate;

The immunity from legal process referred to in Article 18(a) and
		  21(b) of the Ottawa Agreement shall not apply in case of civilian or criminal
		  actions arising from the use of motorvehicles;

Officials and experts of Netherlands nationality shall be granted
		  solely the privileges and immunities mentioned in Article 19 and 23 a, b and c
		  of the Ottawa Agreement;

The General Manager shall notify the Netherlands Government as soon
		  as possible, and thereafter with respect to any change, of the names, grades
		  and addresses of officials and experts;

The General Manager may recruit directly and employ in the
		  Netherlands civilian labour not enjoying international status at local wage
		  rates in the same manner as AFCENT;
